# English language neologism.
Creted by Dave Baron, Gaia Banchelli, Stephen Avis and Vittorio Frangilli for the English version of the Italian book "L'Arciere Eretico" , "The Hereic Archer" written by Vittorio and [Michele Frangilli] in 2005. It translates the Italian language neologism "miratori", in the specific meaning of archers who use long time to aim to the target.
To be used mainly in plural version, can also be an adjective in its single version "sighter"